name: Math.abs()
description: Returns the absolute value of x.
return_value: The absolute value of x. If x is negative (including -0), returns -x. Otherwise, returns x. The result is therefore always a positive number or 0.

name: Math.acos()
description: Returns the arccosine of x.
return_value: The inverse cosine (angle in radians between 0 and Ï, inclusive) of x. If x is less than -1 or greater than 1, returns NaN.

parameters.description: A number between -1 and 1, inclusive, representing the angle's cosine value.

name: Math.acosh()
description: Returns the hyperbolic arccosine of x.
return_value: The inverse hyperbolic cosine of x. If x is less than 1, returns NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number greater than or equal to 1.

name: Math.atan2()
description: Returns the arctangent of the quotient of its arguments.
return_value: The angle in radians (between -Ï and Ï, inclusive) between the positive x-axis and the ray from (0, 0) to the point (x, y).

parameters.name: y

parameters.name: x

name: Math.atanh()
description: Returns the hyperbolic arctangent of x.
return_value: The inverse hyperbolic tangent of x. If x is 1, returns Infinity. If x is -1, returns -Infinity. If x is less than -1 or greater than 1, returns NaN.

name: Math.cbrt()
description: Returns the cube root of x.
return_value: The cube root of x.

name: Math.ceil()
description: Returns the smallest integer greater than or equal to x.
return_value: The smallest integer greater than or equal to x. It's the same value as -Math.floor(-x).

name: Math.clz32()
description: Returns the number of leading zero bits of the 32-bit integer x.
return_value: The number of leading zero bits in the 32-bit binary representation of x.

name: Math.cos()
description: Returns the cosine of x.
return_value: The cosine of x, between -1 and 1, inclusive. If x is Infinity, -Infinity, or NaN, returns NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number representing an angle in radians.

name: Math.cosh()
description: Returns the hyperbolic cosine of x.
return_value: The hyperbolic cosine of x.

name: Math.exp()
description: Returns ex, where x is the argument, and e is Euler's number (2.718â¦, the base of the natural logarithm).
return_value: A nonnegative number representing ex, where e is the base of the natural logarithm.

name: Math.expm1()
description: Returns subtracting 1 from exp(x).
return_value: A number representing ex - 1, where e is the base of the natural logarithm.

name: Math.floor()
description: Returns the largest integer less than or equal to x.
return_value: The largest integer smaller than or equal to x. It's the same value as -Math.ceil(-x).

name: Math.fround()
description: Returns the nearest single precision float representation of x.
return_value: The nearest 32-bit single precision float representation of x.

name: Math.hypot()
description: Returns the square root of the sum of squares of its arguments.
return_value: The square root of the sum of squares of the given arguments. Returns Infinity if any of the arguments is Â±Infinity. Otherwise, if at least one of the arguments is or is converted to NaN, returns NaN. Returns 0 if no arguments are given or all arguments are Â±0.

name: Math.imul()
description: Returns the result of the 32-bit integer multiplication of x and y.
return_value: The result of the C-like 32-bit multiplication of the given arguments.

name: Math.log()
description: Returns the natural logarithm (ãe; also, ã) of x.
return_value: The natural logarithm (base e) of x. If x is Â±0, returns -Infinity. If x < 0, returns NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number greater than or equal to 0.

name: Math.log10()
description: Returns the base-10 logarithm of x.
return_value: The base 10 logarithm of x. If x < 0, returns NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number greater than or equal to 0.

name: Math.log1p()
description: Returns the natural logarithm (ãe; also ã) of 1 + x for the number x.
return_value: The natural logarithm (base e) of x + 1. If x is -1, returns -Infinity. If x < -1, returns NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number greater than or equal to -1.

name: Math.log2()
description: Returns the base-2 logarithm of x.
return_value: The base 2 logarithm of x. If x < 0, returns NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number greater than or equal to 0.

name: Math.max()
description: Returns the largest of zero or more numbers.
return_value: The largest of the given numbers. Returns NaN if any of the parameters is or is converted into NaN. Returns -Infinity if no parameters are provided.

parameters.name: value1
parameters.description: Zero or more numbers among which the largest value will be selected and returned.

name: Math.min()
description: Returns the smallest of zero or more numbers.
return_value: The smallest of the given numbers. Returns NaN if any of the parameters is or is converted into NaN. Returns Infinity if no parameters are provided.

parameters.name: value1
parameters.description: Zero or more numbers among which the lowest value will be selected and returned.

name: Math.pow()
description: Returns base x to the exponent power y (that is, xy).
return_value:
A number representing base taken to the power of exponent. Returns NaN in one of the following cases:

exponent is NaN.
base is NaN and exponent is not 0.
base is Â±1 and exponent is Â±Infinity.
base < 0 and exponent is not an integer.

name: Math.random()
description: Returns a pseudo-random number between 0 and 1.
return_value: A floating-point, pseudo-random number between 0 (inclusive) and 1 (exclusive).

name: Math.round()
description: Returns the value of the number x rounded to the nearest integer.
return_value: The value of x rounded to the nearest integer.

name: Math.sign()
description: Returns the sign of the x, indicating whether x is positive, negative, or zero.
return_value:
A number representing the sign of x:

If x is positive, returns 1.
If x is negative, returns -1.
If x is positive zero, returns 0.
If x is negative zero, returns -0.
Otherwise, returns NaN.

name: Math.sin()
description: Returns the sine of x.
return_value: The sine of x, between -1 and 1, inclusive. If x is Infinity, -Infinity, or NaN, returns NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number representing an angle in radians.

name: Math.sinh()
description: Returns the hyperbolic sine of x.
return_value: The hyperbolic sine of x.

name: Math.sqrt()
description: Returns the positive square root of x.
return_value: The square root of x, a nonnegative number. If x < 0, returns NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number greater than or equal to 0.

name: Math.tan()
description: Returns the tangent of x.
return_value:
The tangent of x. If x is Infinity, -Infinity, or NaN, returns NaN.

Note: Due to floating point precision, it's not possible to obtain the exact value Ï/2, so the result is always finite if not NaN.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: A number representing an angle in radians.

name: Math.tanh()
description: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of x.
return_value: The hyperbolic tangent of x.

name: Math.trunc()
description: Returns the integer portion of x, removing any fractional digits.
return_value: The integer part of x.
